# *Limits*

- Limits quantify what happens to the values of a function as we approach a given point.
- This can be defined as: “***the limit as x goes to 6 of f(x) approaches some value L***”.

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/61bd7333-501e-4ebc-96d3-7b8b716daa64/Untitled.png)

- We can read this as: “***the limit as x goes to 6 of f(x) approaches some value L***”
    - To evaluate this limit, we take points increasingly closer and closer to *6*— as close to 6 as we can get, but not 6 itself! We then evaluate where the function is headed at those points.
- If we look at the limit of a function as x approaches a value from one direction, this is called ***a one-sided limit***.
- For example, we might look at the values of *f(5)*, *f(5.9)*, *f(5.999)* and see if they are trending towards the value of *f(6)*. This is represented as:

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/3450f501-4d46-4455-b72e-b598877e8bdd/Untitled.png)

- We read this as “***the limit as x approaches 6 from the left side approaches some value L***”.
- Whereas if we looked at the values of *f(6.1)*, *f(6.01)*, *f(6.0005)* and see if they are trending towards *f(6)*, we would represent this as:
    
    ![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/ff8b6a5a-9d71-4c3f-b3cd-f15dc4435c60/Untitled.png)
    
- We read this as “***the limit as x goes to 6 from the right side approaches some value L***”.

> The limit as *x* approaches 6 exists only if the limit as *x* approaches 6 from the left side is equal to the limit as *x* approaches 6 from the right side.
> 

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/aa1fc676-b08c-4366-a22d-fd87eaf95635/Untitled.png)

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/ebb91a19-e945-4dd5-b946-38409302dca4/Untitled.png)

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/0a324622-d12e-4a48-8f94-da8f7c0433dd/Untitled.png)

![Untitled](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/deca009c-ecf1-4fdc-817d-9ce6773a72f0/Untitled.png)

